        "created_at": "2016-10-23T13:53:02.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Agreed that the Ramonet rendition is very nice: had it over lunch a few days ago in Burgundy, and was very happy to have six snoozing in the cellar.</p>\n<p>The Fran\u00e7ois Carillon style is rich and gourmand; notably riper than the wines of Jacques Carillon or Louis before the split. It seems to be popular with the French wine press.</p>",
